This is the point in the album, where I begin to remember how F'n amazing it is. Here, I am listening, eager, for the first time: the "10th Anniversary SE", feat all the tracks that weren't on my-- what 13 track, 1997 edition(?). Rock n roll. AND-- all i'd had, for so many years-- a CRAP 128KBps backup i'd made (you know, roommates; after-the-show parties; etc (stolen CD's). OH! How did we ever fall for the idea that 128Kbps was "CD Quality"... (uh, bullshit!). This is SOOOOOooo much better. Thank you, Dave an co. I'm happy now, for a while at least. :-)
